00:00:20.008 --> 00:00:25.396
Welcome! Let’s Talk About Emotions. We all have emotions, and they affect

00:00:25.546 --> 00:00:28.635
how we speak, listen, lead, and respond to life.

00:00:29.108 --> 00:00:33.405
Emotional intelligence helps us understand those feelings, whether it’s joy,

00:00:33.555 --> 00:00:37.445
frustration, or nervous excitement, and handle them with more intention.

00:00:37.595 --> 00:00:41.961
This course will help you know yourself better, manage emotional highs and

00:00:42.111 --> 00:00:45.398
lows, and connect more deeply with people around you.

00:00:45.642 --> 00:00:49.497
It’s not about suppressing emotion. It’s about recognising it, working with

00:00:49.647 --> 00:00:53.375
it, and using it wisely. And to bring this to life, we’ll follow someone

00:00:53.525 --> 00:00:54.501
relatable!

00:00:59.775 --> 00:01:04.641
Meet David. He just started a new job, and he’s full of energy and big ideas.

00:01:04.842 --> 00:01:09.940
He’s smart, enthusiastic, and eager to succeed. But sometimes, his emotions

00:01:10.090 --> 00:01:14.967
get ahead of him. When he’s excited, he jumps into conversations too quickly.

00:01:15.117 --> 00:01:19.669
When he’s praised or happy, he says yes to everything and ends up overwhelmed.

00:01:19.819 --> 00:01:24.278
And in moments of tension, he finds it hard to read the room or respond

00:01:24.428 --> 00:01:25.126
calmly.

00:01:25.608 --> 00:01:29.789
Throughout this course, we’ll follow David’s journey, not to point out what’s

00:01:29.939 --> 00:01:34.398
wrong, but to see how emotional intelligence helps him navigate both the

00:01:34.548 --> 00:01:38.775
positive and the negative sides of his daily life. But let’s start with

00:01:38.925 --> 00:01:39.344
you!

