00:02:12.308 --> 00:02:15.037
Do You Ever Feel Like Your Emotions Are Running the Show?

00:02:15.542 --> 00:02:19.734
Have you ever gotten carried away in a moment, said something you regret,

00:02:19.884 --> 00:02:22.822
or felt so excited you made a hasty decision?

00:02:38.142 --> 00:02:40.035
What Is Emotional Intelligence?

00:02:40.908 --> 00:02:45.657
According to psychologist Daniel Goleman, emotional intelligence is the ability

00:02:45.807 --> 00:02:50.209
to recognize, understand, and manage your own emotions, while also responding

00:02:50.359 --> 00:02:52.229
well to the emotions of others.

00:02:52.675 --> 00:02:59.003
It's helps you stay grounded in moments of pressure, joy, anxiety, or excitement.

00:02:59.153 --> 00:03:03.984
It’s about being intentional, not impulsive, with what you feel and how

00:03:04.134 --> 00:03:08.686
you act.
Most people are not familiar with emotional intelligence; they

00:03:08.836 --> 00:03:12.715
are only familiar with IQ. Both of these are different and very important.

00:03:12.865 --> 00:03:14.259
let’s compare them.

00:03:19.508 --> 00:03:23.723
Emotional Intelligence which is known as EI, vs Intelligence Quotient, which

00:03:23.873 --> 00:03:25.117
is known as IQ.

00:03:25.308 --> 00:03:30.742
IQ measures thinking and logic. It helps with test scores, technical skills,

00:03:30.892 --> 00:03:32.310
and solving problems.

00:03:32.842 --> 00:03:37.638
EI deals with self-awareness, emotion, and connection with others.
IQ might

00:03:37.788 --> 00:03:42.351
help you get a job. EI helps you keep it and thrive while working with people.

00:03:42.501 --> 00:03:46.856
It’s easy to think intelligence is the only thing that matters. However,

00:03:47.006 --> 00:03:51.047
being emotionally intelligent can also help you become emotionally aware

00:03:51.197 --> 00:03:55.378
and connect with your surroundings. These are part of the reason EI matters

00:03:55.528 --> 00:03:56.423
most times.

00:04:03.375 --> 00:04:05.129
Why It Matters in Real Life!

00:04:06.642 --> 00:04:11.438
It helps you manage frustration, but also excitement, enthusiasm, and joy.

00:04:11.588 --> 00:04:16.987
Without it, emotions can drive overreactions, impulsive decisions, or emotional

00:04:17.137 --> 00:04:21.376
crashes. With it, you enjoy the highs, handle the lows, and stay steady

00:04:21.526 --> 00:04:25.846
when it matters most. So, how do you spot emotional intelligence in action?

00:04:25.996 --> 00:04:27.994
Let’s look at five key skills.

00:04:33.275 --> 00:04:35.819
The Building Blocks of Emotional Intelligence.

00:04:36.508 --> 00:04:41.397
According to Daniel Goleman, emotional intelligence includes five core skills.

00:04:41.547 --> 00:04:44.531
Let’s explore each one with a real-life example.

00:04:44.742 --> 00:04:50.060
Self-Awareness: You realise you’re dominating a conversation and shift the

00:04:50.210 --> 00:04:54.600
spotlight to others.
That’s self-awareness—knowing what you feel and how

00:04:54.750 --> 00:04:56.295
it might affect others.

00:04:56.475 --> 00:05:00.888
Self-Regulation: You feel irritated but pause before reacting and say, 'Let’s

00:05:01.038 --> 00:05:05.613
figure this out.'
That’s self-regulation—managing how you express emotion.

00:05:06.008 --> 00:05:09.863
Motivation: You’re working toward a tough goal, and even when things get

00:05:10.013 --> 00:05:13.939
frustrating, you stay focused because it matters to you. That’s motivation,

00:05:14.089 --> 00:05:16.446
using emotion to fuel progress.

00:05:16.642 --> 00:05:21.310
Empathy: You notice a friend is quiet and ask, 'Want to talk?'
That’s empathy,

00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:23.969
tuning in to how others might feel.

00:05:24.175 --> 00:05:29.993
Social Skills: During a team meeting, you help smooth over a tense moment

00:05:30.143 --> 00:05:34.567
by encouraging collaboration and making sure everyone is heard.
That’s

00:05:34.717 --> 00:05:40.290
social skill, navigating relationships and guiding group dynamics.
Emotional

00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:44.377
intelligence isn’t about one big moment, it’s about the small, everyday

00:05:44.527 --> 00:05:49.427
choices you make. It shows up in how you respond to praise, handle pressure,

00:05:49.577 --> 00:05:53.421
and treat people when no one’s looking. Let’s see how well you can spot

00:05:53.571 --> 00:05:54.489
it in action.

